-- D.R. Horton orders rise 4 pct as housing demand picks up
-- By Sagarika Jaisinghani in Bangalore
-- Tue Jan 28, 2014 07:09AM EST
-- None



Jan 28 (Reuters) - D.R. Horton Inc <DHI.N>, the largest U.S. homebuilder, reported a 4 percent rise in orders in the first quarter as housing demand picked up after slowing over the summer.

Net income almost doubled to $123.2 million, or 36 cents per share, in the quarter ended Dec. 31 from $66.3 million, or 20 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw1bKqXqa]